<subSubSection id="DEBD18DCD302EF353120088132DFBEAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="36459036EC2594CE876AA64ED8B69400" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44DB33E0D78343E7C3921ADF71D028B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Named to honor the eminent mycologist Enric Descals Callisen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A0C3307BF8AB259D10504A370543E762" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2059039D3FF44FC3F96211813316BD1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7CECF2AB802154998AB30E73DCBAE0D" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
Sexual morph: Stromata forming black fusiform spots that merge with each other with age, forming an erumpent black mass visible at the naked eye, 2-10 
<normalizedToken id="6A3AF0A0BBD0537D80D41F0A1AD079F5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.5 mm in size, with the long axis broken at the top revealing the ostioles of pseudothecia. Ascomata pseudothecia, subglobose with a flattened base, arranged in rows, brown to dark brown, 150-220 
<normalizedToken id="30E2C9A8D1C1967DB1D725B3611E8CA1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high 
<normalizedToken id="EFFCE7FBB2790B8EE1B079B0DD62288C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
150-250 
<normalizedToken id="4C6B9C3B48F0D882A08E8DFBBC2718B9" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide (n = 20). Peridium with several layers of cells arranged in textura angularis, with a conspicuous ostiole 50-80 
<normalizedToken id="12EA509482AE5A424DBB62AC817EEDD1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, periphysate. Hamathecium paraphyses hyphae-like, septate, hyaline. Asci cylindrical, clavate, with a short or indistinct pedicel, with rounded apices, measuring (73
<normalizedToken id="F8EEF4B43F5010CD2D2E897ADF0DAD9B" originalValue="–)82–95(–">-)82-95(-</normalizedToken>
111) 
<normalizedToken id="F0632A54B5B9B3E84345760CB3813133" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(16
<normalizedToken id="803C717E119AE52076EBF2F2AE147144" originalValue="–)17–20(–">-)17-20(-</normalizedToken>
23) 
<normalizedToken id="E538D873C7EECF548BBA38B6FF0F6BD1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 30). Ascospores uniseriate to biseriate, hyaline, smooth-walled, apiosporic, composed of a large curved upper cell and smaller lower cell, fusiform to slightly curved in shape with narrowly rounded ends, guttulated, sometimes with a thick gelatinous sheath, (17
<normalizedToken id="20D1655994F91EBBD2DAE47FEC503ECC" originalValue="–)18–22(–">-)18-22(-</normalizedToken>
24) 
<normalizedToken id="DF417F192E94375101652065D0A25BA2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(6
<normalizedToken id="218F8A6D67D52EC2B96BD286E2EBF8BF" originalValue="–)7–9(–">-)7-9(-</normalizedToken>
10) 
<normalizedToken id="D8C5302DC2FD4EC39285E7BB622B2603" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, and a basal cell 3-5 
<normalizedToken id="FC7370DDEC1C64D32A897B0BBDEC0728" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n = 45). Asexual morph: Mycelium hyaline, septate, branched, hyphae 1.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken id="4E5E4C279D202614C04912223651FE86" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter Conidiophores reduced to the conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells solitary on hyphae, ampuliform, hyaline to brown, 5 
<normalizedToken id="BC4822FC783468037FBBB13C95B2CB92" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 
<normalizedToken id="59F67266A90EEAAD0941F715D2CAF837" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia brown, smooth, guttulate, globose to ellipsoid (5
<normalizedToken id="257A6EB5B0D2861B21EDFDE895009561" originalValue="–)7(–">-)7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="6500E5D7EB5B618A51C97A0731A8F369" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long (n = 20) in face view, lenticular with a paler equatorial slit and 6-7 
<normalizedToken id="E4AE496FBB2322DDB19FEEE83C80721F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long in side view (n = 10). Sterile cells elongated, sometimes mixed among conidia. Culture characteristics: ascospores germinating on MEA 2% within 24-48 h. Colonies flat, spreading, with sparse aerial mycelium, pale siena.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="38F86EDDC29E882293F58A10D9CBD5F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph id="022E450381EA71923832485DDF9CB976" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E943F3762ADD45F83F64C7D03DEB0DA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="2F9075B93E22D9080E0B4FB3C8725A37" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium descalsii" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="descalsii">Arthrinium descalsii</taxonomicName>
is closely related with 
<taxonomicName id="2EDC82A21A87AED843FE56AE95D86F54" genus="A." lsidName="A. phragmitis" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="phragmitis">A. phragmitis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EE99EDBAE6CB1EC76D16108457E01041" genus="A." lsidName="A. balearicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="balearicum">A. balearicum</taxonomicName>
. It was found in the Mediterranean grass 
<taxonomicName id="482DFC87937268760453694431096434" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ampelodesmos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ampelodesmos mauritanicus" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritanicus">Ampelodesmos mauritanicus</taxonomicName>
, although additional samples are needed before concluding if it could be exclusively associated with this endemic host. Ascospore size is often smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName id="A2DB4FD1578F59FF7CC2F5BE2176D9E8" genus="A." lsidName="A. balearicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="balearicum">A. balearicum</taxonomicName>
, (23
<normalizedToken id="F8B11F33FC55E2B462D3B000D337F60D" originalValue="–)26–30(–">-)26-30(-</normalizedToken>
32) 
<normalizedToken id="09123CFF71B56171199EAA7D20421BE4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(7
<normalizedToken id="87F9AE263365EB9066D8E15FF38B2366" originalValue="–)9–10(–">-)9-10(-</normalizedToken>
12) 
<normalizedToken id="E2228586AA471488C3F91EB035A0D6A0" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, but it matches that reported in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="26F173995806635D2741F2422CAC08A9" genus="A." lsidName="A. phragmitis" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="phragmitis">A. phragmitis</taxonomicName>
, (20
<normalizedToken id="151B50983B408596760858E4B69BB64F" originalValue="–)22–24(–">-)22-24(-</normalizedToken>
25) 
<normalizedToken id="43A918F32676AF537775E0D10F5AE599" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(7
<normalizedToken id="784A1409E1D458C9BE7C506C949AADB8" originalValue="–)8–9(–">-)8-9(-</normalizedToken>
10) 
<normalizedToken id="42C5F6136BEE50F22D24CF2878DD7E91" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. However, the conidiophores of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC5825AFFE9026D8BAB8FB53006E41" genus="A." lsidName="A. descalsii" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="descalsii">A. descalsii</taxonomicName>
are reduced to conidiogenous cells, while those of 
<taxonomicName id="6D41BB1BB989DE931FD396DC1DC360AB" genus="A." lsidName="A. phragmitis" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="phragmitis">A. phragmitis</taxonomicName>
measure about 10-45 
<normalizedToken id="C9C809D5756613428F5135C6B89291D8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 
<normalizedToken id="6E2FB6D1AE3D4106D4BAFD52A4B8DBB8" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, and conidia are slightly smaller in face view, measuring (5
<normalizedToken id="1F477B1BC7AF926E44230D9147B2B5C9" originalValue="–)7(–">-)7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="CB9FE9D5C311E910C0CA06D42D39F2DB" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long in 
<taxonomicName id="5EFBC7B1B57EAAE5190F261ABD14CAAC" genus="A." lsidName="A. descalsii" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="descalsii">A. descalsii</taxonomicName>
and up to 8
<normalizedToken id="308147D3F1751DF02D51439AF53D7CE2" originalValue="–10(–">-10(-</normalizedToken>
11) 
<normalizedToken id="E3DE3B70C7594E6F48D4347BDA8AD3BB" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="201774FB318D261930649549F6748A2B" genus="A." lsidName="A. phragmitis" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="phragmitis">A. phragmitis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AABF693DCB7C0EF15F4881FB63038771" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="CB07D81ECF263B57F2C10C9B4A279F34" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7DC0F55F7653F5A8907D312662089AA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
